info.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth

info.flavor_text: "The Lord Aragorn I hold to be my liege lord, whether he claim it or no. His wish is to me a command."

name: Riders of Rohan (The Lord of the Rings Commander Precon Decklist)
info.name: Field of Ruin
info.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.

info.flavor_text:
"There's some devilry at work in the Shire."
—Sam

name: Riders of Rohan (The Lord of the Rings Commander Precon Decklist)

info.flavor_text:
When winter first begins to bite
and stones crack in the frosty night,
when pools are black and trees are bare,

info.oracle_text: When Banishing Light enters, exile target nonland permanent an opponent controls until Banishing Light leaves the battlefield.
info.flavor_text: Before all went Aragorn with the Flame of the West—Andúril, like a new fire kindled, Narsil reforged as deadly as of old. And upon his brow was the Star of Elendil.

info.oracle_text: Whenever Théoden, King of Rohan or another Human you control enters, target creature gains double strike until end of turn.
info.flavor_text: "Dark have been my dreams of late, but I feel new-awakened. I only fear that already you have come too late, Gandalf."

—Elrond
